owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: DesignNote
owl:AnnotationProperty.obo:IAO_0000115: A property representing notations made by NCI vocabulary curators. They are intended to provide supplemental, unstructured information to the user or additional insight about the concept.

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: Contributing_Source
owl:AnnotationProperty.obo:IAO_0000115: A property is used to indicate when a non-EVS entity has contributed to, and has a stake in, a concept. This is used where such entities, within or outside NCI, have indicated the need to be able to track their own concepts. A single concept can have multiple instances of this property if multiple entities have such a defined stake.

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: Legacy Concept Name
owl:AnnotationProperty.obo:IAO_0000115: A property representing a retired unique concept identifier created and stored as Concept Name by legacy EVS software. Use of these values was long discouraged, but continued as late as 2009 when creation of new values ceased and Concept Name was retired. Legacy values are intended solely to help resolve and update earlier coding.

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: definition
owl:AnnotationProperty.obo:IAO_0000115: A property representing the English language definitions of what NCI means by the concept. They may also include information about the definition's source and attribution in a form that can easily be interpreted by software.

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: Maps_To
owl:AnnotationProperty.obo:IAO_0000115: A property representing that a term in another terminology has been mapped to a term in NCIt and describes the relationship between the mapped terms.

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: xRef
owl:AnnotationProperty.obo:IAO_0000115: A property representing a reference to an identical or very similar object in another database.

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: Is_Value_For_GDC_Property
owl:AnnotationProperty.obo:IAO_0000115: An association that that connects a concept representing a GDC value to any associated GDC property concept(s).

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: has exact synonym
owl:AnnotationProperty.obo:IAO_0000115: A property representing a fully qualified synonym, contains the string, term type, source, and an optional source code if appropriate. Each subfield is deliniated to facilitate interpretation by software.

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: Has_OORO_PC_Value
owl:AnnotationProperty.obo:IAO_0000115: An association specifying the Values for a specific OORO Prostate Cancer (PC) Attribute.

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: ALT_DEFINITION
owl:AnnotationProperty.obo:IAO_0000115: A property representing the English language definition of a concept from a source other than NCI.

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: Semantic_Type
owl:AnnotationProperty.obo:IAO_0000115: A property that represents a description of the sort of thing or category to which a concept belongs in the context of the UMLS semantic network.
owl:AnnotationProperty.obo:NCIT_P98: In general, applying semantic types aids in allowing users (or computer programs) to draw conclusions about concepts by virtue of the categories to which they have been assigned. We use a set of semantic types developed for the UMLS Metathesaurus. There are currently 134 semantic types in the UMLS.

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: in subset
owl:AnnotationProperty.obo:IAO_0000115: An association that connects the concept defining a particular terminology subset with concepts that belong to this subset.

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: code
owl:AnnotationProperty.obo:IAO_0000115: A property representing a concept unique identifier within the NCI Enterprise Vocabulary Service's NCI Thesaurus.

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: NCI_META_CUI
owl:AnnotationProperty.obo:IAO_0000115: A property representing the concept unique identifier (CUI) for those concepts that appear in NCI Metathesaurus but not in the National Library of Medicine Unified Medical Language System (NLM UMLS).

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: Display_Name
owl:AnnotationProperty.obo:IAO_0000115: A property representing an alternative Preferred Name for use in some NCI systems.

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: FDA_Table
owl:AnnotationProperty.obo:IAO_0000115: A property used to flag terms that are part of an FDA data standard manual, including Route of Administration, Dosage Form, Package Type and Potency.

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: Preferred_Name
owl:AnnotationProperty.obo:IAO_0000115: A property representing the word or phrase that NCI uses by preference to refer to the concept.

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: UMLS_CUI
owl:AnnotationProperty.obo:IAO_0000115: A property representing the concept unique identifier (CUI) assigned by the National Library of Medicine (NLM). If a concept in any NCI-maintained knowledgebase exists in the NLM Unified Medical Language System (UMLS), NCI includes the NLM CUI among the information we provide about the concept.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Consent Waiver
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The release from the requirement to obtain informed consent during a study that is granted by Human Subject Protection committee for a research institution for a protocol that is being reviewed by the Institutional Review Board.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Person Role Title
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: An identifying designation assigned to an individual that corresponds with their function.
owl:Class.obo:NCIT_P325: An identifying designation assigned to an individual that corresponds with their function. May include but not limited to Principal Investigator, SubInvestigator, Study Coordinator, Sponsor Project Manager, CRO Project Manager, Data Manager.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Artificial Intelligence
owl:Class.obo:NCIT_P325: A system's ability to correctly interpret external data, to learn from such data, and to use those learnings to achieve specific goals and tasks through flexible adaptation. [Kaplan, A; Haenlein, M (1 January 2019) Business Horizons; IEEE-USA POSITION STATEMENT. Artificial Intelligence Research, Development & Regulation Adopted by the IEEE-USA, Board of Directors (February 2017)] See also machine learning, deep learning, natural language processing, synthetic data.
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Artificial intelligence is the branch of computer science that deals with writing computer programs that can solve problems creatively.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Child
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: An age group comprised of individuals who are not yet an adult. The specific cut-off age will vary by purpose.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Real-world Data
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Data relating to patient health status and/or the delivery of health care routinely collected from sources other than traditional clinical trials. Examples of sources include data derived from electronic health records (EHRs); medical claims and billing data; data from product and disease registries; patient-generated data, including from in-home-use settings; and data gathered from other sources that can inform on health status, such as mobile devices. (21 U.S.C. 355g(b)).5 and Framework for FDA's Real-World Evidence Program December 2018)
owl:Class.obo:NCIT_P325: Data relating to patient health status and/or the delivery of health care routinely collected from sources other than traditional clinical trials. NOTE: Examples of sources include data derived from electronic health records (EHRs); medical claims and billing data; data from product and disease registries; patient-generated data, including from in-home-use settings; and data gathered from other sources that can inform on health status, such as mobile devices. [After 21 U.S.C. 355g(b)).5 and Framework for FDA's Real-World Evidence Program December 2018; FDA Draft Guidance, Data Standards for Drug and Biological Product Submissions Containing Real-World Data, OCTOBER 2021] See also Real-World Evidence (RWE)

Data relating to patient health status and/or the delivery of health care routinely collected from sources other than traditional clinical trials. NOTE: Examples of sources include data derived from electronic health records (EHRs); medical claims and billing data; data from product and disease registries; patient-generated data, including from in-home-use settings; and data gathered from other sources that can inform on health status, such as mobile devices. [After 21 U.S.C. 355g(b)).5 and Framework for FDA's Real-World Evidence Program December 2018] See also Real-World Evidence (RWE)
Health-related information collected from many different types of records and used for research purposes. (https://mrctcenter.org/glossaryterm/real-world-data-rwd/)

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Health Status
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The state of a subject's mental or physical condition.
owl:Class.obo:NCIT_P325: The state of a subject's mental or physical condition.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Population Group
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A group of individuals united by a common factor (e.g., geographic location, ethnicity, disease, age, gender)
owl:Class.obo:NCIT_P325: Any finite or infinite collection of subjects from which a sample is drawn for a study to obtain estimates for values that would be obtained if the entire population were sampled. [AMA style Manual]

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Research Ethics
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The branch of ethics that studies moral values in research sciences and practices.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Title
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: An identifying designation.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Personal Attribute
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The distinguishing qualities or prominent aspects of an individual person.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Conceptual Entity
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: An organizational header for concepts representing mostly abstract entities.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Age Related Group
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Subgroups of populations based on age.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Disability
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Any physical or mental impairment that interferes with an individual's ability to perform desired activities.
owl:Class.obo:NCIT_P325: Any physical or mental impairment that interferes with an individual's ability to perform desired activities.

High level categorizations of disabilities having an impact on basic functioning. This is important for research and health care policy using social determinants of health (SDOH). Values should be as identified by patient.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Benefit
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The positive effects of something.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Consent
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Permission to do something.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Status
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A condition or state at a particular time.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Value
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A numerical quantity measured or assigned or computed.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Qualifier
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A term that helps define and render a concept unique.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Authorization
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Decision of the competent authorities in form of a letter, document, or verbal or electronic form, that confirms that somebody has permission to do something or be somewhere, e.g. to realize a given project.
owl:Class.obo:NCIT_P325: The process of giving someone permission to do or have something. In multi-user computer systems, a system administrator defines for the system which users are allowed access to the system and what privileges of use are permitted. [HL7 EHR-S FM Glossary of Terms, 2010].

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Group
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Any number of entities (members) considered as a unit.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Deidentification
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Removal of text elements that would make data individually identifiable.
owl:Class.obo:NCIT_P325: The process of removing potentially identifying data or data elements to render data into a form that does not identify individuals and where identification is not likely to take place. NOTE: A general term for a process of removing the association between a set of identifying data and the data subject. Examples of potentially identifying data include name, birth date, social security number, home address, telephone number, e-mail address, medical record numbers, health plan beneficiary numbers, full-face photographic images). [After ISO/TS 25237: 2008 - Health Informatics - Pseudonymization; HIPAA: 45 CFR, 164.514] See also anonymization.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Data Value
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The information contained in a data field. It may represent a numeric quantity, a textual characterization, a date or time measurement, or some other state, depending on the nature of the attribute.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Anonymous
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Having no known name or identity or known source.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Resolution
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A means of finding a solution to a problem, or a means of finding agreement or harmony.
